President Biden welcomed President Moon of the Republic of Korea to the White House for a ceremony honoring Colonel Ralph Puckett Jr. for his bravery and valor during the Korean War. President Biden awarded Colonel Puckett the Medal of Honor, recognizing his long-overdue act of valor. The President praised Colonel Puckett's courage and leadership, highlighting his dedication to his men and his unwavering commitment to the mission. President Moon also expressed his gratitude to Colonel Puckett and all the Korean War veterans for their sacrifices in defending freedom and democracy in Korea. The ceremony underscored the enduring partnership between the United States and the Republic of Korea, as well as the strong bond between the two countries.